HEADWORD: Ebonite
<hw>Eb"on*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
hard, black variety of vulcanite. It may be cut and polished, and is
used for many small articles, as combs and buttons, and for insulating
material in electric apparatus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ebonize</ent>⟦br⟧
